{
  "text": "The evaluation of velocity fields depends on dynamic estimation of a discrepancy (density ratio or density difference) between the pushforward distribution q t and the target distribution p. Density-ratio and density-difference fitting with the Bregman score provides a unified framework for such discrepancy estimation [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] without estimating each probability distribution separately.",
  "correct_citation": {
